markdown <<MARKDOWN
# AI-Generated Images

#### AI-generated images are fine to use in AI-related contexts, such as professional learning about a curriculum unit that uses an AI chatbot. However, we want to build trust with our users by being transparent about our use of AI.

* #### Start by searching for existing photos, visuals, and illustrations to center real students and teachers using our products. AI-generated images can be used as necessary.
* #### Attribute AI-generated images appropriately, citing the image engine. Ideally, AI images should be generated by software that Code.org has a license for (such as ChatGPT).
* #### Ensure that AI-generated images of humans are realistic.

### **Example**:
    
<div style="text-align:center;">
    <img src="https://images.code.org/5f643df03b3565e7a1c367ae2a3b468b-image-1710871493815.04.49 AM.png" alt="A brown owl sits on a branch." style="display:block; margin:auto; width: 250px">
    <p style="font-size:10pt; margin-top:10px;"><b>Note</b>: AI image generated using Adobe Firefly from the prompt "Brown owl in a forest".</p>
</div>

MARKDOWN
